Write an overdispersed Poisson GLM in STAN

library(rstan)
## Loading required package: Rcpp
## Loading required package: inline
## 
## Attaching package: 'inline'
## 
## The following object is masked from 'package:Rcpp':
## 
##     registerPlugin
## 
## rstan (Version 2.5.0, packaged: 2014-10-22 14:19:22 UTC, GitRev: e52c66f42e81)
model <- "
// overdispersed Poisson parameterized 
// see Gelman and Hill (2007)
data {
  int<lower=1> N;       // number of observations
  int<lower=0> p;
  matrix[N, p] X;       // predictor
  int<lower=0> y[N];    // response
} transformed data {
  vector[p] J;
  matrix[p, p] I_p;
  // calculate placeholder values
  J <- rep_vector(0, p);
  I_p <- diag_matrix(rep_vector(1, p));
}
parameters {
  real<lower=0> tau;   // Poisson dispersion parameter
  vector[p] beta;      // Poisson mean parameters
  vector[N] epsilon;   // Poisson deviances
} transformed parameters {
  vector[N] means;     // Poisson means
  means <- exp(X * beta + epsilon);
} model {
  // priors:
  tau ~ cauchy(0, 20);
  beta ~ multi_normal(J, 100 * I_p);
  // data model:
  for(i in 1:N){
    epsilon[i] ~ normal(0, tau);
  }
  y ~ poisson_log(means);
}
"
write(model, file = "../stanModels/overdispersedPoisson-glm.stan")
sm <- stan_model("../stanModels/overdispersedPoisson-glm.stan")

Simulate some Data

set.seed(123)
N <- 80
tau <- 1
# beta <- c(1, 2, -1, 1, -2, -1)
beta <- c(2, -1, 1, -2, -1)
x0 <- rep(1, N)
x1 <- c(rep(1, N/2), rep(0, N/2)) ## Indicator for net size
x2 <- rep(c(rep(1, 10), rep(0, 30)), 2) ## Indicator for July
x3 <- rep(c(rep(0, 10), rep(1, 20), rep(0, 10)), 2) ## Indicator for August
# x4 <- rep(c(rep(0, 30), rep(1, 10)), 2) ## Indicator for September
x12 <- x1 * x2 ## Interaction between net size and July
x13 <- x1 * x3 ## Interaction between net size and August
# X <- cbind(x0, x1, x2, x3, x12, x13)
X <- cbind(x1, x2, x3, x12, x13)
y <- rpois(N, exp(X %*% beta + rnorm(N, 0, tau)))
layout(matrix(c(1, 1, 2, 3), 2, 2, byrow=TRUE))
hist(y)
hist(y[x1 == 0])
hist(y[x1 == 1])

Fit the Model

m <- sampling(sm, data = list(N = N, y = y, X = X, p=dim(X)[2]),
  pars = c("beta", "tau"),
  iter = 5000, chains = 4)

Plot traceplots

rstan::traceplot(m, inc_warmup = FALSE)

Plot fitted vs.simulated values

e <- rstan::extract(m, pars = c("beta", "tau"))
true_pars <- c(beta = beta, tau = tau)
library(lme4)
## Loading required package: Matrix
## 
## Attaching package: 'Matrix'
## 
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     crossprod, tcrossprod
obs_effect<-1:N
overdisp.fit <- glmer(y ~ X - 1 + (1|obs_effect), family=poisson)
coefs <- c(overdisp.fit@beta, overdisp.fit@theta)
par(mfrow = c(3, 3))
for(i in 1:2) {
  if(i == 1) {
#     for(j in 1:6) {
    for(j in 1:5) {
      plot(density(e[[i]][,j]), main = names(true_pars)[i + j - 1])
      abline(v = true_pars[i + j - 1], lwd = 2, col = "grey", lty = 2)
      abline(v = coefs[i + j - 1], lwd = 3, col = "red")
    }
  } else if(i == 2) {
    plot(density(e[[i]]), main = names(true_pars)[i + j - 1])
    abline(v = true_pars[i + j - 1], lwd = 2, col = "grey", lty = 2)
    abline(v = coefs[i + j - 1], lwd = 3, col = "red")
  }
}
